## The Complexity of Estrangement: No One-Size-Fits-All

Experts emphasize that estrangement is not a monolithic phenomenon. Some adult children may make inappropriate choices in estranging themselves, while others make justified decisions based on objectively harmful circumstances. Similarly, some parents are victims of unjustified estrangement, while others have contributed to the breakdown of the relationship ([WeHaveKids, 2022](https://wehavekids.com/family-relationships/adult-child-estranged-reasons)).

Joshua Coleman, a psychologist specializing in estrangement, notes multiple pathways to estrangement, including the child’s need to blame someone for life outcomes, mental illness in the child, and tensions involving the child’s spouse ([Next Avenue, 2021](https://www.nextavenue.org/adult-children-parents-estrangement/)).

## Implications for Reconciliation

Because estrangement is often initiated by the adult child, parents are typically the ones who must take the first steps toward reconciliation. Successful reconnection is frequently attributed to parents’ efforts to:

- Take responsibility for past harms
- Show empathy for the child’s perspective and feelings
- Express willingness to change problematic behaviors
- Accept boundaries around privacy, contact frequency, and time with grandchildren

Avoiding debates about “right” and “wrong” and acknowledging at least some truth in the child’s perspective is crucial ([The Atlantic, 2021](https://www.theatlantic.com/family/archive/2021/01/why-parents-and-kids-get-estranged/617612/)).

## Conclusion

Adult children become estranged from their parents for a complex interplay of reasons, prominently including past abuse, toxic behaviors, value conflicts, mental health issues, and family dynamics such as divorce and caregiving disputes. The divergence in perspectives between parents and children about the causes of estrangement presents significant challenges for healing. Recognizing the multifactorial nature of estrangement and fostering empathy and accountability on both sides are essential for any hope of reconciliation.

